Sentencas: SOFC short stacks with thin-film electrolyte anode-supported cells were operated for up to similar to 3,000 h and post-test characterized.
Titulo: Chromium-Related Degradation of Thin-Film Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stacks

Sentencas: The cells consisted of thin electrolyte films (<= 3 mu m) and LSCF or LSC cathodes.
Titulo: Chromium-Related Degradation of Thin-Film Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stacks

Sentencas: Typical manganese-oxide chromium evaporation protection layers and perovsldtic cathode contact layers were used.
Titulo: Chromium-Related Degradation of Thin-Film Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stacks

Sentencas: Operating parameters were: temperatures between 600 degrees C and 750 degrees C, a current density of 500 mA/km(2), hydrogen with 20% water vapor as fuel, and a fuel utilization of similar to 40%.
Titulo: Chromium-Related Degradation of Thin-Film Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stacks

Sentencas: Microstructural characterization revealed that Cr-containing phases formed at different locations.
Titulo: Chromium-Related Degradation of Thin-Film Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stacks

Sentencas: SEM and TEM analysis of some cells additionally showed microstructural changes within the GDC layer.
Titulo: Chromium-Related Degradation of Thin-Film Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stacks

Sentencas: A possible explanation for the different chromium-containing phase locations based on theoretical assumptions is given.
Titulo: Chromium-Related Degradation of Thin-Film Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stacks
